{
  "number": 1580,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1580",
  "title": "CurrentRefinements: More specific BEM style",
  "body": "Currently I'm fighting with CurrentFilters styles. This is how it looks:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"281\" alt=\"screen shot 2016-11-18 at 14 23 27\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2096101/20431505/96c4312a-ad9a-11e6-997c-20c03386b88c.png\">\r\n\r\nand the code:\r\n\r\n```scss\r\n.ais-CurrentRefinements__item:not(.ais-CurrentRefinements__itemParent) {\r\n  @extend .dib, .br4, .mb2, .mr2, .mt3, .bg-light-blue, .near-white;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.ais-CurrentRefinements__itemParent > .ais-CurrentRefinements__itemLabel {\r\n  display: block;\r\n  @extend .mt3;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.ais-CurrentRefinements__itemLabel {\r\n  @extend .pa0, .pl2;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.ais-CurrentRefinements__itemClear {\r\n  background: none;\r\n  border: none;\r\n  padding: 0.5rem 0.5rem 0.4rem 0.5rem;\r\n\r\n  @extend .v-mid, .pointer;\r\n\r\n  > svg {\r\n    @extend .br-100, .blue, .f6, .dim;\r\n    padding: 2px;\r\n    background-color: white;\r\n    vertical-align: baseline !important;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you can see, the code don't look plain. It could be easy fix adding the correctly specific class, like:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.ais-CurrentRefinements__item:not(.ais-CurrentRefinements__itemParent\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt actually refers the item selected, then need a `ais-CurrentRefinements__itemSelected` class.\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.ais-CurrentRefinements__itemParent > .ais-CurrentRefinements__itemLabel\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt actually refers the facet name, then need `ais-CurrentRefinements__itemsName` class.",
